headline: The Only Remedy for Intel’s Woes May Be a Breakup
summary: To emerge from a yearslong financial and technological rut,  Intel  needs to better compete with chip makers like  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing  It looks increasingly like that will require breaking up the company.  The storied chip maker for decades minted money by designing and making its own chips in its own factories.  Both are contract chip-makers, which meant any of Intel’s competitors in chip design, from  Nvidia  to  Advanced Micro Devices  had access to better factories.
